        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12511",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jayson",
                        "name": "jayson",
                        "displayName": "Jayson Minard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The provided Base-AuthSub.php sample exhibits the same behavior when you fix the bug in the call to get the feed passing in an URI or calling for the base feed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jayson",
                        "name": "jayson",
                        "displayName": "Jayson Minard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-05T02:30:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-05T02:30:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12559",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I cannot reproduce this error.  I confirmed that the Http Client is executing the code from which your error message is generated.  That is, in Zend_Http_Client_Adapter_Socket::read(), in the block that handles responses with the transfer-encoding header == 'chunked'.  But it works for me and does not produce an error.\n\nIs this error reproduceable in your environment?  \n\nI have noticed that sometimes Google's servers don't always respond perfectly.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-07T10:09:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-07T10:09:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14804",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This has received no update in a long time, and the recent redesign of Zend_Gdata may resolve any problems.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-25T21:08:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-25T21:08:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15280",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fuentez",
                        "name": "fuentez",
                        "displayName": "Ramon de la Fuente",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I presume this issue has to do with an issue I'm trying to submit at the moment. It gives the same error but with Zend_Feed (that uses Zend_Http_Client).\n\n-\nAfter some investigation the problem turns out to be a case-sensitivity differance in the variables in line 222 and 223:\n{quote}\n$chunksize = hexdec(chop($line));\nif (dechex($chunksize) != $hexchunksize) {\n{quote}\n\n\nAs a workarround I alter the setting of the $hexchunksize variable in line 220:\n{quote}\n$hexchunksize = strlen($hexchunksize) ? *strtolower*($hexchunksize) : 0;\n{quote}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fuentez",
                        "name": "fuentez",
                        "displayName": "Ramon de la Fuente",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-18T07:52:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-18T07:52:43.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
